<title>JAPAN: SONY, PHILIPS, H-P SEEK NEW DVD-RAM STANDARD - PAPER.</title>
<headline>SONY, PHILIPS, H-P SEEK NEW DVD-RAM STANDARD - PAPER.</headline>
<dateline>TOKYO 1997-08-13</dateline>
<text>
<p>Sony Corp, Philips Electronics NV and Hewlett-Packard Co plan to end their participation in a 10-firm agreement to use a common format for DVD-RAMs (digital video disc random-access memories), the business daily Nihon Keizai Shimbun said on Wednesday.</p>
<p>The three companies intend to seek approval for a separate format from the European Computer Manufacturers Association, the paper said.</p>
<p>A spokesman for Sony could not immediately confirm the report.</p>
